task.summary: All but one test case is working for the extensible hash -- essentially there needs to be a way to deal with local indices that are associated with more than one global index, but that should not be too hard to figure out from this...

Okay this is working, it needs to be cleaned up a lot, but everything about the extensible-hash seems to work now. One problem, zero seems to corrupt when we insert too much for whatever reason, and I have no idea why...

So apparently there was no real problem except that we were running out of buffers, upped the buffer number and all my tests worked. So insert is good. Added a delete method and also cleaned everything else up in addition.

Couple new things, disk ios and run time is actually reporting out correctly now -- needed to swap over to the heuristic query planner instead of the basic one. Good news: extensible has is consistently out-performing static hash and b-tree indexes, bad news: no idex is massively outperforming all of them, and I don't know why?? This is a bizarre issue, but I am assuming because it is outperforming the indices we didn't touch that this will be fine.
